    "body": "error log:\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)   File \"/root/miniconda3/lib/python3.12/site-packages/flashinfer/sampling.py\", line 980, in top_k_top_p_sampling_from_logits\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)     masked_logits = top_k_mask_logits(logits, top_k)\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)                     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)   File \"/root/miniconda3/lib/python3.12/site-packages/flashinfer/sampling.py\", line 1300, in top_k_mask_logits\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)     return get_sampling_module().top_k_mask_logits(\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)            ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)   File \"/root/miniconda3/lib/python3.12/site-packages/flashinfer/sampling.py\", line 47, in get_sampling_module\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)     module = gen_sampling_module().build_and_load()\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)              ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)   File \"/root/miniconda3/lib/python3.12/site-packages/flashinfer/sampling.py\", line 35, in gen_sampling_module\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)     return gen_jit_spec(\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)            ^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)   File \"/root/miniconda3/lib/python3.12/site-packages/flashinfer/jit/core.py\", line 175, in gen_jit_spec\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)     check_cuda_arch()\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)   File \"/root/miniconda3/lib/python3.12/site-packages/flashinfer/jit/core.py\", line 55, in check_cuda_arch\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)     elif major == 7 and minor.isdigit():\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455)                         ^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n(EngineCore_DP0 pid=1455) AttributeError: 'int' object has no attribute 'isdigit'\r\n\r\n## 📌 Description\r\n\r\nIn the Compute Capability judgment logic, the \"isdigit\" method of the number type was incorrectly called, causing a crash in the test. Remove the incorrect method call \"isdigit\" of the number type.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Related Issues\r\n\r\nnone\r\n\r\n## 🚀 Pull Request Checklist\r\n\r\nThank you for contributing to FlashInfer! Before we review your pull request, please make sure the following items are complete.\r\n\r\n### ✅ Pre-commit Checks\r\n\r\n- [ ] I have installed `pre-commit` by running `pip install pre-commit` (or used your preferred method).\r\n- [ ] I have installed the hooks with `pre-commit install`.\r\n- [ ] I have run the hooks manually with `pre-commit run --all-files` and fixed any reported issues.\r\n\r\n> If you are unsure about how to set up `pre-commit`, see [the pre-commit documentation](https://pre-commit.com/).\r\n\r\n## 🧪 Tests\r\n\r\n- [ ] Tests have been added or updated as needed.\r\n- [ ] All tests are passing (`unittest`, etc.).\r\n\r\n## Reviewer Notes\r\n\r\n<!-- Optional: anything you'd like reviewers to focus on, concerns, etc. -->\r\n",
